{"name": "solana-trading-bot", "metadata": {"name": "solana-trading-bot", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["solana", "pycryptodome", "semantic-types", "requests"], "summary": "The aim of this project is to provide a powerful tool for trading on Web3's most renowned exchanges", "upload_time": 1734909986}, "documentation": ["# Solana On-Chain Trading Bot (Very Immature Now)\n\nThis project is owned by [@handsomevictor](https://github.com/handsomevictor), a Chinese boy living in Paris.\n\n## Introduction\n\nThe aim of this project is to provide a powerful tool for trading on Web3's most renowned exchanges, such as\n[JUP](https://jup.ag/). JUP is primarily used for swapping tokens, and this tool focuses on utilizing it for trading\nrather than traditional limit orders.\n\n**Disclaimer**: This project, owned solely by [@handsomevictor](https://github.com/handsomevictor), offers open-source\nstrategies without warranty. The author holds no responsibility for any losses incurred while using this project.\n\n## Usage\n\nBefore using the project, ensure you have created a wallet, transferred some SOL or other tokens to it, and placed the\npublic and private keys in the environment variables. The project utilizes these keys to sign transactions.\n\n```python\nUSER_PUBLIC_KEY = os.environ.get(\"TEST_USER_PUBLIC_KEY\")\nUSER_PRIVATE_KEY = os.environ.get(\"TEST_SOLANA_USER_PRIVATE_KEY\")\n```\n\n## How to Run\n\nExecute [transaction_executor.py](trading_bot%2Ftransaction_executor.py) in `./trading_bot`.\n\n## Example Calculation\n\nAssume your Solana wallet holds 1 SOL and 1 USDC, and you want to swap 0.1 SOL for USDC. Assuming a gas fee of 0.00007\nSOL and a price of 1 SOL = 100 USDC, the result would be:\n\n- SOL: 1 - 0.1 (swapping amount in SOL) - 0.00007 (gas fee) = 0.89993\n- USDC: 1 + 0.1 (swapping amount in SOL) * 100 (exchange rate) = 2\n\n## Email Notification\n\nIf you want to use it, register an account on Outlook (or any other email service) and enable the SMTP server,\nand change the following parameters in `./tools/resources.py` or add them to your environment variables:\n\n- SMTP_SERVER\n- SMTP_PORT\n- SENDER_EMAIL\n- EMAIL_PASSWORD\n\n## Reminders\n\n- Never trade all your SOL. Always leave some for gas fees.\n- No matter if a trade is made or not, as long as it's sent to the blockchain, a gas fee will be charged (range is\n  usually 0.00006 - 0.00015 SOL but can be higher).\n\n## Resourcess\n\nThis project utilizes the documentation provided by [Jup](https://station.jup.ag/docs/apis/swap-api)\nand [solana-py](https://michaelhly.com/solana-py/), also took some pieces of code\nfrom [0xTaoDev](https://github.com/0xTaoDev/jupiter-python-cli)\n\n## Data Source\n\nReal-time data is sourced from Kaiko and the Binance API. However, only Kaiko data is used for building trading\nstrategies. If you're interested in leveraging Kaiko data, feel free to reach out. Note that it's not free.\n\n## Some Good Blockchain Analytics Websites\n\n- [BirdEye](https://birdeye.so/)\n- [Defillama](https://defillama.com/airdrops?chain=Solana)\n- [ArkhamIntelligence](https://platform.arkhamintelligence.com/explorer/entity/grayscale)\n- [Dune](https://dune.com/etaetaeta/pyth-stakers-over-time)\n\nDate: Feb. 13, 2024\n"], "modules": [{"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.signals.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.signals", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.save_records_to_influxdb", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "measurement_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bucket_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "records_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.INFLUXDB_ORG", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.INFLUXDB_TOKEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.INFLUXDB_URL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.client", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.write_api", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.TMP_DATABASE_DIR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.base", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.quote", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.measurement_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.all_strategies.strategy_buy_dip.influxdb_tool.bucket_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-bot.trading_bot", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "solana-trading-